# Financial Risk Market Weighted Average Interest Rate Percent

## identifier
de15102

## type
float

## definition
This is the weighted sum of individual interest rates, where the weights used are the corresponding balances expressed as a share of the total balance. The interest rate is the contractual rate to be paid to or received by the customer/counterparty/debtholder. It excludes any fees charged to the customer/counterparty/debtholder.

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=FinancialRisk.Market.WeightedAverageInterestRate.Percent
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.34
- period=instant
